added.title: Hafo Safo
added.description: The Titans travel to the hipster neighborhood of Silver Lake, California to help solve a mystery.

added.title: BBRAE Part 1
added.description: Beast Boy writes a song to tell Raven how he feels about her.

added.title: BBRAE Part 2
added.description: Beast Boy goes on tour with his song, but this upsets Raven.

added.title: Head Fruit
added.description: When Beast Boy's head starts to rattle, Robin suggests that he should find a hobby so that his brain will stop shrinking. Beast Boy and his brain agree to take up gardening.

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Debt
added.description: Gumball resolves to save Mr Robinson's life during Elmore's Senior Talent Show.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

added.title: The Club
added.description: When Gumball rejects "The Rejects Club", the rejects wreak their revenge.

added.title: The Car
added.description: Gumball and Darwin accidentally destroy Mr Robinson's new car...or do they?

added.title: Billy Bajillions
added.description: In Aspen, Colorado, Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max are on a hike to find the Forgeti, but when they realize they've stumbled upon Billy Billions own "Winter in July" ski resort, Ben must battle Billy, with an assist from the Forgeti itself.

added.title: Buggin' the Buggs
added.description: Team Tennyson travel to the Chrysalen Institute for some hot yoga and good vibes, only to find that the Bugg Brothers are on vacation, too, but are the sneaky insectoids really on holiday, or just cooking up yet another silly, yet high stakes scheme?

added.title: Baby Buktu
added.description: When attacked in the jungle, Team Tennyson is saved by a toddler who looks eerily similar to Tim Buktu, but when they discover it really is a pint sized version of the nefarious globetrotter, Ben knows there's another threat looming, Nanny Nightmare!

added.title: Mutiny for the Bounty
added.description: While Phil and Grandpa Max tune-up the Omni-Copter, a restless Ben takes the Rustbuggy off road, but when he is suddenly captured by Textrax and the hunter takes the bounty for himself, our hero must not only escape but avoid the wrath of the double-crossed Kraab and Sixsix!

added.title: Buggy Out
added.description: After winning a Sumo Slammers Champion belt, Ben returns to the Rustbucket to find his prize in the arms of Kevin, but when his rival hijacks the Rustbuggy instead, our hero must stop at nothing to get back what's rightfully his!

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.title: Stink Bomb
added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: Crisis at Elder Rock
added.description: Tragedy strikes the Creek when the Elders get trapped under Elder Rock, and it's up to Craig, Kelsey and JP to rescue them.

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: The Children of the Dog
added.description: Craig has tried to convince his family to get a dog for years but has never been successful, but he may have a chance if he follows the guidance of a charismatic creek kid and her three step program.

added.title: Exercising the Demons
added.description: When a severe screen addiction turns the kids into lazy deadbeats, Chef brings in a professional to whip them into shape.

added.title: Pudding the Planet First
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Supply Mom
added.description: When Chef's mom becomes the supply teacher for a day Duncan replaces Chef's to-do list with one of his own.

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a funny formula that will land him a comedic in a movie.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple & Onion try to finish a story before the book disappears forever.

added.title: Appleoni
added.description: Apple and Onion want credit for creating a new dance craze.

added.title: Baby Pepito
added.description: When a mysterious "baby" appears on Chata's doorstep, V&V are convinced it's not what it seems.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 1
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 2
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 3
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 4
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #AdventuresInBunnysitting
added.description: Zee asks Kara to look after her two magical bunnies, which quickly start to multiply, wreaking havoc all across Metropolis.

added.title: ThunderSlobs
added.description: Tygra's feeling unappreciated by the other ThunderCats so he starts hanging out with Mumm-Ra and cleaning his Black Pyramid?! Whaaaaaaat?

added.title: Working Grrrl
added.description: Cheetara is the fastest living person in the universe until Monkian beats her in a race?! Now Cheetara has to find something else to be the best at and the rest of the ThunderCats have to find out how Monkian got so darn fast!

added.title: Mandora - The Evil Chaser
added.description: Lion-O "accidentally" releases a whole space prison-full of space criminals and winds up on the wrong side of the law. On the right side of the law is Mandora the Evil Chaser, a no nonsense space cop! Lion-O's gonna have to work real hard to prove he's not a criminal, just a little bit of an oaf!

added.title: Dr. Dometome
added.description: Lion-O is tasked with mapping the beaches of Third Earth, which leads to him somehow draining the oceans of all water entirely. Woops! But a mysterious scientist with a robotic frog says they can fix everything by traveling under the earth, which is just the kinda crazy adventure Lion-O is all about!

added.title: Study Time
added.description: Lion-O never pays attention during Tygra's training sessions so when he's asked to do a pop quiz on "sword magic" he accidentally opens a portal to the Astral Plane and releases the Nether Witch! The Witch imprisons Lion-O and Tygra in her nightmare realm and it's gonna take a lot of studying to figure out a way home. Wonder if the Astral Plane has any great teachers lying around.

added.title: Breezy
added.description: With a friendly bee named Breezy as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

added.title: Dentist
added.description: Finn's aching tooth leaves him with no other option but to go to the dentist.

added.title: Bad Little Boy
added.description: The princesses are sick and tired of Ice King's crazy Fionna & Cake stories, so Marceline stops by the Ice Kingdom to show him how it's done.

added.title: Blade of Grass
added.description: Finn and Jake decide it's time for Finn to get a new sword. Finn reluctantly buys a grass sword from a mysterious old man but the sword turns out to be cursed.

added.title: Betty
added.description: In Wizard City, a magic spell backfires and turns Ice King back into Simon.

added.title: Dumptown USA
added.description: Benson is going to fire Mordecai if Rigby can't bring him back from a bizarre land of dudes also known as Dumptown USA.

added.title: Donut Factory Holiday
added.description: The guys have to return a VHS copy of their favorite terrible movie or else pay a huge late fee.

added.title: Gary's Synthesizer
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby unplug some cables in an old synthesizer. They have to travel to the planet of Synthos in order to re-connect them and bring Gary back to life.

added.title: Favorite Shirt
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, and High Five Ghost have to somehow get Muscle Man's favorite shirt back on him before he wakes up.

added.title: Deez Keys
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby need to make a deal with the scientists to get Benson's car keys back.

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Brains TV
added.description: After a marathon of classic sitcom episodes, Clarence becomes stuck as alter-ego "Clarry," an obnoxiously overacting sitcom version of himself. It's up to his friends and family to help him snap out of it, or face life with a new Clarence.

added.title: Etiquette Clarence
added.description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

added.title: Video Store
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo visit their local video store to rent a movie, but discover it's all rented out! Each of them have a different idea of what tape to bring home, and must enlist the help of a tie breaker to figure it out.

added.title: Anywhere but Sumo
added.description: When Clarence realizes Sumo has made a new group of friends at his new school, he becomes jealous and confused. Will Clarence accept a school life void of Sumo, or scheme his way into making their friendship work?

added.title: Under Wraps
added.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

added.title: Billy Billones
added.description: En Aspen, Colorado, Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max van de excursión para encontrar al Olvideti. Pero cuando se encuentran con la pista artificial de esquí de Billy Billones, Ben debe luchar contra Billy con la ayuda del propio Olvideti.

added.title: Magnus P.I.
added.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

added.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
added.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

added.title: The Mysterious Revenger/Wynton vs. Lia
added.description: The Mysterious Revenger: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!/Wynton Vs. Lia: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.

added.title: Watch It!
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Paseo en Buggy
added.description: Después de ganar un cinturón como campeón de Luchadores de Sumo, Ben regresa al Rustbucket y encuentra su premio en los brazos de Kevin. Pero cuando su rival secuestra el Rustbuggy, inuestro héroe no debe detenerse ante nada para recuperar lo que le pertenece legítimamente!

added.title: Huelga por el Botin
added.description: Mientras Phil y el abuelo Max afinan el Omni-Copter, Ben, inquieto, saca el Rustbuggy de la carretera. Pero cuando de repente es capturado por Tetrax, nuestro héroe no solo debe escapar, sino también evitar la ira de los traicioneros Kraab y SeiSeis.

added.title: Molestando a los Bichos
added.description: El equipo de Tennyson viaja al Instituto Crisalín en busca de yoga a altas temperaturas y buenas vibraciones, solo para descubrir que los hermanos Bicho también están de vacaciones. Pero ¿los astutos insectoides están realmente de vacaciones, o están tramando otro de sus tontos planes?

added.title: Bebe Baktu
added.description: Cuando es atacado en la jungla, el equipo Tennyson es salvado por un niño que se parece inquietantemente a Tim Buktu, pero cuando descubren que realmente es una versión en miniatura del infame trotamundos, Ben sabe que se avecina otra amenaza, Nanny Nightmare!

added.title: Cambio de Temporada
added.description: Cuando nuestros héroes regresan de sus vacaciones, K.O. se horroriza al descubrir que las cosas cambiaron.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Mal Radical
added.description: Cuando llega un nuevo reemplazo, K.O. y Dendy deciden que necesitan recuperar a su antiguo profesor.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: The So-Bad-Ical
added.description: When a new substitute shows up, KO and Dendy decide they need to get their old teacher back.

added.title: Apointa a la Plaza
added.description: Cuando la plaza se infesta de pegote, P.O.I.N.T. llega para contener la situación.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Point to the Plaza
added.description: When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.

added.title: Red Action to the Future
added.description: When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.

added.title: Campista Profuga
added.description: Una fugitiva de un campamento de verano termina en el Tronco, pero Craig sospecha que su historia puede no ser lo que parece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bomba apestosa
added.description: La explosión accidental de una bomba de olor causa que todos los niños evacúen el Arroyo, pero Craig toma la responsabilidad de rescatar a aquellos dejados atrás en el hedor.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Super Black Friday
added.description: After being forced to work on a holiday, KO, Rad and Enid take a stand.

added.title: Ninos del Perro
added.description: Craig ha intentado que su familia adopte un perro durante años, pero nunca lo logró. Puede que ahora tenga una oportunidad si sigue los consejos de un carismático niño del bosque y su programa de tres pasos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: Crisis en la roca de Ancianos
added.description: Una tragedia azota al Arroyo cuando los Ancianos quedan atrapados bajo la Roca Anciana. Ahora Craig, Kelsey y JP deben rescatarlos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la merecedora
added.description: Cuando Kelsey demuele una pared de la casa de Craig, su padre le quita la espada. Por eso, Kelsey les pide ayuda a Craig y a JP para que le demuestren a su padre que aún la merece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Super Dia de Ofertas
added.description: Cuando los obligan a trabajar en un día festivo, KO, Rad y Enid se pronuncian en contra de la medida.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: Accion Roja al Futuro
added.description: Cuando convocan a Acción Roja a una batalla épica en el futuro, Enid no está segura de lo que debe hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Primera parte
added.description: En el episodio estreno de cuatro partes de la serie, seis chicas comunes y corrientes se conocen y descubren que tienen poderes extraordinarios. Deciden unir sus fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Segunda parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 2 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Tercera parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 3 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #La dulce justicia - Cuarta parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 4 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LosConejosMágicos
added.description: Cuando Zee le pide a Kara que cuide a sus dos conejitos mágicos, pronto comienzan a multiplicarse y a desatar el caos por toda Metrópolis.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Dodge City
added.description: Axel embraces the spirit of dodgeball to stop Madcap and Princess SugarSalt's battle over who is the better villain from spilling over into Zoe and Cleo's argument over who is the better coach!

added.title: The Best Team
added.description: When Madcap and his minions crash a soapbox derby, the team must stop the baddies and help Axel - stuck in a car with Luka - cross the finish line!

added.title: Joyride
added.description: At a rummage sale with Uncle Andrew, Axel and Zoe must stop Madcap from turning her long-lost tank toy, Joyride, into an agent of mayhem!

added.title: Mystery Noise
added.description: It's Sleepover Dream Night in the RV and the gang just wants to get some sleep to dream their dreams, but when a mysterious noise keeps them awake, their grip on sanity begins slipping.

added.title: Savage Axel
added.description: Bearbarian helps Axel get in touch with his wild side as Orangutank "liberates" nature from an apartment building - tossing potted plants of all sizes out the window and onto innocent bystanders below!

added.title: The Scratch Pack
added.description: Axel and the team must run damage control after a loose spark of Minergy accidentally turns Zoe's old toys - a set of cute squishy kittens - into a pack of snarling beasts.

added.title: Lightfall Part 1
added.description: The mysterious Lord Obsidian calls Mega Man a traitor to robots and challenges him to a duel. An overconfident Mega Man is humbled by this mysterious new villain.

added.title: Viral Spiral
added.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

added.title: Perfect Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid become perfect by turning him into a robot.  But when the robot tries to destroy him for being imperfect, Uncle Grandpa goes on the run.

added.title: Lightfall Part 2
added.description: Lord Obsidian attacks the Lighthouse, but Mega Man overcomes his insecurity and works with his family to repel the big bad, who's rescued at the last second by a mysterious lieutenant, Namagem.

added.title: Rush to Greatness
added.description: Rush puts his new battle upgrades to the test in a battle with Wave Man.

added.title: Swish
added.description: Namagem attacks Mega Man using a variety of powers, revealing that they both can replicate schematics. However, Namagem can carry more than three at a time! The true beginning of the mysterious villain's arc begins here.

added.title: Minus Mini
added.description: When Mega Mini is kidnapped by Blasto Woman, Mega Man must track down his missing partner without the full use of his own systems.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: A young girl's suppressed sense of humor breeds evil that can only be defeated with the help of Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Prison Break
added.description: When Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve's prank calling lands them in an intergalactic prison, they must work together to escape.

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Bengeance is Mine
added.description: Vilgax' former lackey Psyphon is elated when his master returns.

added.title: Animo Crackers
added.description: Dr. Animo from the future comes back to the present to help himself defeat Ben once and for all. (Introducing new Ben alien, Gutrot.)

added.title: New Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa gives a kid a haircut that is too cool for school.

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: El Mejor Equipo
added.description: Cuando Madcap y sus secuaces chocan un derby de caja de jabón, el equipo debe detener a los malos y ayudar a Axel, atrapado en un automóvil con Luka, a cruzar la línea de meta.

added.title: La traicion
added.description: Tigro se siente poco apreciado por los demás Thundercats...i¿y por eso empieza a pasar tiempo con Mumm-Ra y a limpiar su Pirámide Negra?!

added.title: Rio de Oro
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla intentan terminar un cuento antes de que el libro desaparezca para siempre.

added.title: Los Gatos Rascadores
added.description: Axel y el equipo deben ejecutar el control de daños después de que una chispa suelta de Minergy accidentalmente convierta los viejos juguetes de Zoe, un conjunto de lindos gatitos blandos, en una manada de bestias gruñendo.

added.title: Joyride
added.description: iEn una venta de artículos usados ​​con el tío Andrew, Axel y Zoe deben evitar que Madcap convierta su juguete tanque perdido, Joyride, en un agente de caos!

added.title: El Salvaje Axel
added.description: Bearbarian ayuda a Axel a ponerse en contacto con su lado salvaje mientras Orangutank "libera" la naturaleza de un edificio de apartamentos, arrojando plantas en macetas de todos los tamaños por la ventana y hacia personas inocentes que se encuentran debajo.

added.title: La Formula de Manzana
